```julia
function clean_column(col)
    return replace(lowercase(strip(col)), r"\s|-" => "_")
end
```

This function takes a string `col` as input and returns the cleaned version of the column name. It first strips any leading or trailing whitespace using `strip`, then lowercases the entire string with `lowercase`. Finally, it replaces any spaces and hyphens with an underscore using `replace` with a regular expression pattern. The regex pattern `\s|-` matches any space or dash character, and `"_"` is used as the replacement for this pattern.
